@startuml
title Viaverse Runtime Request / Service Communication — Sequence Diagram

actor Client
participant "CloudFront/WAF" as Edge
participant "ALB/Ingress" as ALB
participant "API Gateway / BFF" as Gateway
participant "Domain Service" as Service
database "PostgreSQL/Redis" as DB
queue "Kafka/Outbox" as Kafka
participant "OTel/Logs/Metrics" as OTel

Client -> Edge : HTTPS request
Edge -> ALB : WAF passed
ALB -> Gateway : route to BFF
Gateway -> Service : authorized command/query
Service -> DB : transaction + outbox insert
Service -> Kafka : publish via outbox relay
Service -> OTel : trace/log/metric
Service --> Gateway : response DTO
Gateway --> Client : redacted response
Kafka ..> Service : async consumer in other service

note bottom
Synchronous calls go through gateway/BFF for external clients.
Domain-to-domain consistency uses events/outbox where possible;
avoid distributed transactions.
end note
@enduml
